README - docs for my ThinkPad X301 environment: usage and maintenance

file management:
- view drives:			df -h
- used space (current dir):	du -h
- standard commands:		ls, cd, mkdir, touch, cat
- editing:			nano <file>

programs:
- browsing the web		w3m <url>
- sending mail:			mail -s "<subject>" (-a "<attachment>") "<recipient>"
- hangouts:			hangups
	sign-in:		python scripts/hangups_manual_login.py
		# dev tools > application > cookies: look for "client_id"
- reddit:			rtv
- opening a gui:		startx /usr/bin/<program>
	- close:		(sudo) killall /usr/bin/<program>
			OR	(sudo) killall /usr/bin/xinit 

network management:
- start network manager:	(sudo) /usr/bin/NetworkManager --no-daemon
	# start in tty0 or alternate process
	process script:		scripts/nm_start.sh
		stop process:	scripts/nm_stop.sh
- list networks:		nmcli dev wifi
- connect to a network:		nmcli dev wifi connect <ssid> (password <password>)
	already added		nmcli connection up <ssid>
- add a network			nmcli connection add type wifi con-name "<ssid>" ...

power management:
- battery info:			(sudo) tlp stat
- charge thresholds:		(sudo) tlp setcharge <start> <end> [device]
- usage:			(sudo) powertop
- optimization:			(sudo) powertop --auto-tune

display:
- brightness:			(sudo) setpci -s 00:02.0 F4.B-<brightness (hex)>

settings:
- grub				(sudo) nano /etc/default/grub
	update:			(sudo) grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
